The paper deals with complexity and algorithms in the distributed LOCAL model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the study of LCL problems, which are a type of graph labeling problem, and the use of randomized and deterministic algorithms, which are topics in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the Lovasz local lemma problem, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and has connections to probabilistic algorithms. Finally, the paper establishes a time hierarchy theorem, which is a fundamental result in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and is relevant to the study of algorithmic time complexity.
